First Solar Sells Project to NextEra, GE After Getting Guarantee

-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 
2011-09-30T19:47:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/first-solar-sells-project-to-nextera-ge-after-getting-guarantee.html
First Solar Inc. (FSLR) , the world’s
largest maker of thin-film solar panels, sold a 550-megawatt
project in California to  NextEra Energy Inc. (NEE)  and  General
Electric Co. (GE)   First Solar did not give a price for the deal in a
statement today. The U.S. Energy Department announced today a
$1.46 billion loan guarantee for the Tempe, Arizona-based
company’s Desert Sunlight project.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  